Libya is to close three migrant and refugee detention centres after criticism from the UN over squalid conditions and inadequate food supplies. Two of the centres are in the coastal cities of Misrata and Khoms. The third is in Tajura, a suburb of the capital Tripoli. Forces loyal to the warlord Khalifa Haftar hit that facility in an air strike a month ago, killing at least 52 people. Al Jazeera's Raheela Mahomed reports. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter  